description:
Under certain circumstances, the code assist feature is eating too much code. The following class demonstrates the issue:

public class X {
void bar(X x) {
baz(x.foo());
}

int foo() {
return 5;
}

void baz(int i, int j) {
}
}

To make the program correct, a parameter needs to be added to the 'baz' call in the 'bar' method. The expected behavior is that the code assist should not eat the code when providing suggestions.
